cancer_history_summary:
Age: 70
Sex: Male
Cancer type: Prostate cancer
Histology: Adenocarcinoma, Gleason score 9 (4+5)
Current extent: Metastatic castration‑resistant disease, bone‑dominant (osteoblastic lesions in T10 vertebral body and left ischial wing); no visceral metastases
Biomarkers: 
- Serial PSA: 0.4 ng/mL (≈3 mo prior), 0.9 ng/mL (initiation of abiraterone), 2.6 ng/mL (05/2025) indicating ≥50 % rise;
- Total testosterone consistently castrate (15 ng/dL);
- Alkaline phosphatase 112 U/L (within reference);
- Liver function tests normal (AST 28 U/L, ALT 32 U/L);
- Renal function normal (Creatinine 0.92 mg/dL);
- Pending comprehensive germline/somatic NGS panel for DDR genes (BRCA1/2, ATM, PALB2, etc.);
- No recorded PSMA PET or AR‑V7 assessment.
Treatment history:
# Date unavailable – Surgery: radical retropubic prostatectomy with extended pelvic lymph node dissection; pathology Gleason 9 pT3a N1 M0.
# Commenced continuous luteinizing hormone‑releasing hormone agonist (leuprolide depot) shortly thereafter; ongoing throughout course.
# Mid‑2024 (approximately 12 months prior to 06/2025) – Start of abiraterone acetate 1000 mg po daily plus prednisone 5 mg bid for mCRPC; tolerability good except intermittent hot flashes and development of Grade 2 hypertension managed with amlodipine 5 mg daily. Best response: transient PSA stabilization, subsequently biochemical progression (rise to 2.6 ng/mL).
# 19 Jun 2025 – Switch from abiraterone to enzalutamide 160 mg po daily; discontinuation of abiraterone and gradual tap­er of prednisone scheduled. Monitoring labs and PSA set for 4‑week follow‑up.
Planned/not yet instituted:
- Zoledronic acid 4 mg iv q12 wk for skeletal protection (awaiting dental clearance);
- Baseline repeat CBC/LFT/Renal panels within 1 week of enzalutamide initiation;
- Follow‑up bone scintigraphy in 12 weeks;
- Molecular profiling of archived tumour/cfDNA for DDR mutations to evaluate suitability for PARP inhibition.
